---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Hero from "../components/Hero.astro";
import Show from "../components/Show.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <Hero heroImage="/src/assets/past.jpg" objectPosition="center 40%" />
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-slate-300 p-8 md:p-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-16">
      <Show
        title="Lines"
        date="Fall 2025"
        authorLabel="An original musical written by company member"
        author="Violet Trachtenberg"
      >
        <p>
          This play investigates the complexities of legacy, and gives honor to
          our
          <span class="italic font-medium"
            >cringy and vulnerable tweenage selves</span
          >. To borrow from Paula Vogel: "This is a play about the gifts we
          receive from the people who harm us."
        </p>
      </Show>
      <Show title="Variety Show" date="Spring 2025">
        <p>
          Featuring works by Tom Stoppard, Paula Vogel, Julia Cho, Jose Llana,
          William Finn, Claude-Michel Sch√∂nberg, Terry Bisson, and company
          member Noam Samuel
        </p>
      </Show>
      <Show
        title="Bros in the Wild"
        date="Fall 2024"
        authorLabel="An original musical written by company member"
        author="Sara Saavedra"
      >
        <p>
          A heartwarming tale of friendship and adventure, "Bros in the Wild" is
          a story of characters whose sincere care for each other is plainly
          known. This musical explores relationships of all shapes and sizes,
          intertwined with a touch of mystical whimsy. And written in a mere
          three weeks!
        </p>
      </Show>
      <Show
        title="Nightmaretime and The Truth"
        date="Spring 2024"
        authorLabel="Two original one-act plays written by friend of the company"
        author="Emily Elyse"
      >
        <p>
          A fascination with psychological unraveling; the marrying of
          unassuming everyday experiences with the mythic; an obsession with
          women who are misguided or wronged... these are just a few things to
          be discovered in these two plays. Though often dark, mysterious, and
          neurotic, Emily's stories also carry a deep tenderness and sharp wit,
          exploring the complexity of human morality, and questioning why we
          make the choices we do.
        </p>
      </Show>
      <Show
        title="In Good Time"
        date="Fall 2023"
        authorLabel="An original musical written by company member"
        author="Nat Lista"
      >
        <p>
          The musical that got us started! A heartfelt and magical tale about
          friendship and confronting your past... literally!
        </p>
      </Show>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
